function (struct Initiative_Legislative_Lib.Law_Project storage pointer,uint256) view returns (bytes memory,uint256[] memory,uint256,uint256,address)

Add_Item(address,bytes32,uint256,bytes[].details: Function can be called by a citizen to add function calls to a proposition that he has already created (He have to be the author of the proposition).  Caller must approve {FunctionCall_Price} multiplied by the number of function call he wants to add to the proposition.

params.Indexs: array of Proposition's function call list indexs to inser new function call (contained in {New_Items}) to. {New_Items} and {Indexs} have the same length.
params.New_Items: Array of new function calls to add to the Proposition.
params.referendum_key: Id of the referendum proposition the caller wants to add function calls to. The Id is obtained by hashing the Title with the Description of the law project.
params.register_address: Address of the register concerned by the referendum project.

Add_Law_Project(address,bytes,bytes).details: Function can be called by any citizen to submit a new law project. Caller must approve {Law_Initialisation_Price} DemoCoin token for Agora contract

params.Description: Text explaining the spirit and generals goals of the referendum proposition. Can be an hash.
params.Title: Title of the Referendum Proposition. Can be an hash.
params.register_address: Address of the register contract the law proposition is about. The address must be contained in Referendums_Registers mapping.

Add_Proposal(address,bytes32,uint256,uin.details: Function can be called by a citizen to submit a corpus of function calls propositions to an existing pending law project. Caller must approve {FunctionCall_Price} DemoCoin Token multiplied by the number of function call contained in the proposition, token for Delegation contract.

params.Description: Text to justify the new proposal. Can be an hash.
params.New_Function_Call: List of new function calls added by the caller. For each element of the New_Function_Call array, caller must set a 0 element in {Parent_Proposals_Reuse} array at the index he want the custom function call to be positioned
params.Parent: Id of the parent proposition the caller wants to attach his proposition to. It's the parent proposition in the proposal tree. If there isn't any proposition in the tree we want to attach the new proposition to, we set Parent to 0
params.Parent_Proposals_Reuse: List of Parent's function calls index we want to reuse in the new proposition. Function calls are ordered in the order we want them to be executed. 0 elements correspond to new function calls that have to be added by the caller in {New_Function_Call} argument.
params.referendum_key: Id of the referendum proposition the caller wants to add a proposition to. The Id is obtained by hashing the Title with the Description of the referendum proposition.
params.register_address: Address of the register concerned by the referendum project.

Create_Register_Referendum(address,uint8.details: Add a new register under Agora's control. Register's address is added as a {Referendum_Register} struct.

params.register_address: Address of the register contract to add
params.register_type: Type of the new register ({Status} enum)

End_Proposition_Stage(address,bytes32).details: Function can be called by any citizen to end the proposition stage if it's finished. If there are enough signatures then we pass to the Voting stage, else the referendum proposition is aborted.

params.register_address: Address of the register contract the Referendum proposition is about. The address must be contained in Referendums_Registers mapping.

End_Vote(address,bytes32).details: Function can be called by any citizen to end the voting stage if it's finished. If the winning proposal id is >0 then the proposal is adopted and can be executed, else if the default proposition is chosen, the referendum proposition is rejected.

params.register_address: Address of the register contract the Referendum proposition is about.

Execute_Law(address,bytes32,uint256).details: Once the referendum proposition has been adopted (ADOPTED value of {Status} enum) then any citizen can call this function to execute all or some of the remaining function call of the winning proposition.  For the Referendum proposition to be fully executed all function call have to be executed.

params.num_function_call_ToExecute: Number of function calls to execute.
params.register_address: Address of the register contract the Referendum proposition is about.

Get_Law_Results(bytes32).details: Get results of a Referendum proposition.

params.key: Id of the law project tha contains the proposal

returns.Receipts: Results of function calls to register functions.
returns.Winning_Proposal: Id of the proposal that has been voted by citizens.

Get_Proposal(bytes32,uint256).details: Get informations about a proposal ({Corpus_Proposal} structure of {Initiative_Legislative_Lib} library) of a law project ({Law_Project} structure of {Initiative_Legislative_Lib} library.

params.id: Id of the proposal in the law project
params.key: Id of the law project tha contains the proposal

returns.author: Account that has submited the proposal.
returns.childrens: List of Proposal's children in the Proposal tree
returns.description: Text describing the spirit and goals of the proposal.
returns.func_call_counter: Number of function call contained in {function_calls}.
returns.function_calls: List of function calls proposed in the Proposal.
returns.parent: Proposal's parent in the Proposal Tree.

Get_Referendum_Register(address).details: Get globals informations about a Register contract ruled by Agora: The last version of Parameters related to the Register contract, it's institution type and the list of referendums (represented by their Ids) that are related to it.

params.register_address: Address of the corresponding Register Contract

returns.list_referendums: List of referendum Id that are related to the Register

Get_Referendum_Register_Parameters(addre.details: Get Parameters related to a register Contract ruled by Agora. It return a {Referendum_Parameters} structure

params.register_address: Address of the corresponding Register Contract

Get_Voter_Reward(address,bytes32).details: Once the referendum proposition has been executed (EXECUTED value of {status} enum), each citizen that has voted can get his DemoCoin token reward. If proposition proposition had a validation stage, then accounts must have voted AND validated their vote for getting their rewards.

params.register_address: Address of the register contract the Referendum proposition is about.

Set_Constitution(address).details: The function Allows to change the Constitution contract the current Institution obey to. The function is only callable by the {Constitution_Address}

params.new_constitution: Address of the new Constitution contract.

Sign_Petition(address,bytes32).details: Function can be called by any citizen to a Referendum proposition petition. A citizen can sign for a specific Referendum proposition only once.

params.referendum_key: Id of the referendum proposition the caller wants to sign. The Id is obtained by hashing the Title with the Description of the law project.
params.register_address: Address of the register contract the Referendum proposition is about. The address must be contained in Referendums_Registers mapping.

Update_Register_Referendum_Parameters(ad.details: Update parameters of referendums related to a specific register. Parameters are registered in a {Referendum_Parameters} struct

params.FunctionCall_Price: Amount of DemoCoin token to pay for each new function call of a function call corpus proposal submission.
params.Ivote_address: Address of the IVote contract used in the voting and validation stage
params.Law_Initialisation_Price: Amount of DemoCoin token to pay to submit a new Referendum proposition.
params.Required_Petition_Rate: The minimum ratio of citizens signatures required to submit the referendum proposition as a referendum to all citizens.

params.Name: Name of the Agora contract
params.citizen_address: Address of the {Citizens_Register} contract of the Web3 Direct Democracy project
params.token_address: Address of the {DemoCoin} contract of the Web3 Direct Democracy project

Referendums.details: Mapping of {Referendum} structure corresponding to contract's referendum projects (pending, aborted and passed)

Constitution_Address().notice: Address of the constitution of the DAO

Total_Token_To_Redistribute().notice: Token amount consummed for emmiting propositions during Petition stage and not yet redistributed

userdoc.notice: In the ancient Greece the Agora was the public place where the population used to gather and which  was the center of social, economic and political life of the city. Etymologically, Agora means «gathering place», «Assembly».  In a Web3 Direct Democracy project, the Agora is the contract used to implement direct democracy via a legislative referendum of people initiative. There is a single Agora contract in a Web3 Direct Democracy and all citizens can take part in it's democratic process.
